HEADWORD: Labidometer
<hw>Lab`i*dom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>labi`s</grk>, <grk>-i`dos</grk>, a forceps + <ets>meter</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>labidometre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A forceps with
a measuring attachment for ascertaining the size of the fetal
head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

